  "The velocity at which the object moves across the surface": "",
  "The Greek letter μ (mu) represents the coefficient of friction. It is a dimensionless number that depends on the types of surfaces in contact. A higher μ means more friction. There are two types: μₛ (static) and μₖ (kinetic).": "",
