  "Friction opposes relative motion — it acts in the direction opposite to the way the surfaces slide (or would slide) against each other. If a box slides to the right, kinetic friction acts to the left. If you push a box to the right but it does not move, static friction acts to the left.": "",
  "A student tries to push a heavy desk across the floor but it does not move. The student pushes with 40 N. What is the static friction force?": "",
